## Steps

### step 1
id: navigate-to-accounts
instruction: Click "Accounts" in the main sidebar.
success_criteria: You are on the Accounts page showing a card grid of your billing accounts. Each card shows the account name, billing NPI, account type, provider count, and location count.
anchor: accounts-nav-link
on_success: next
on_stuck: The "Accounts" link is in the left sidebar. If you do not see it, check that you have the right permissions — Admin role is required to manage accounts.

### step 2
id: find-account
instruction: Locate the account you want to view. Use the search bar at the top to search by account name or NPI if you have many accounts.
success_criteria: The account card you are looking for is visible.
anchor: accounts-search-bar
on_success: next
on_stuck: Type any part of the account name or the 10-digit NPI into the search bar to filter the list.

### step 3
id: open-account-detail
instruction: Click the account card to open the account detail page.
success_criteria: You are on the account detail page showing the account header with NPI and account type, and two tabs: Providers and Locations.
anchor: account-card
on_success: next
on_stuck: Click anywhere on the card to open it.

### step 4
id: explore-tabs
instruction: Click the "Providers" tab to see all clinicians billing under this account, or click the "Locations" tab to see all service sites linked to this account.
success_criteria: The selected tab is active and showing the list of providers or locations associated with this billing NPI.
anchor: providers-tab
on_success: completion
on_stuck: The two tabs — Providers and Locations — are at the top of the account detail page just below the header card.

## Completion Message
you're in the account detail view. from here you can review which providers and locations are linked to this billing NPI. if you need to add a new location, try the add-location flow.

